<p:sld xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" xmlns:p="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/presentationml/2006/main" xmlns:r="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships"><p:cSld><p:spTree><p:nvGrpSpPr><p:cNvPr id="1" name=""/><p:cNvGrpSpPr/><p:nvPr/></p:nvGrpSpPr><p:grpSpPr/><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="2" name="Title 1"/><p:cNvSpPr><a:spLocks noGrp="1"/></p:cNvSpPr><p:nvPr><p:ph type="title"/></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr/><p:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:r><a:t>3. Core Architecture: The Transpiler</a:t></a:r></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="3" name="Content Placeholder 2"/><p:cNvSpPr><a:spLocks noGrp="1"/></p:cNvSpPr><p:nvPr><p:ph idx="1"/></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr/><p:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:r><a:t>What is a Source-to-Source Compiler (Transpiler)?</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:t>- Translates source code from one high-level programming language to another.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:t>- Afaan Oromoo -&gt; Python.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:t>- It does NOT compile directly to machine code or bytecode.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:t>- This allows us to stand on the shoulders of giants (Python's runtime).</a:t></a:r></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr></p:sld>